6:
When you had pasture, then you became full;
\q and when you were filled, your heart became lifted up.
\q For that reason you forgot me.

7:
I will become like a lion to them;
\q like a leopard I will watch along the path.
\q

9:
I will destroy you, Israel;
\q who will be able to help you?
\q

12:
Ephraim's iniquity has been stored up;
\q his guilt has been stored up.
\q
